<lb/><space extent="3" unit="words"/><date when="1881-09-06">Sept. 6/81</date>.</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">Sir,</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="1" unit="words"/>I have to acknowledge
<lb/>the receipt of your letter of
<lb/><date when="1881-09-05">yesterday's date</date>, for which
<lb/>please accept my thanks.
<lb/>You may rest assured
<lb/>that the &#xa3;2 therein
<lb/>contained will be put to the
<lb/>good use for which it is
<lb/>intended. I also enclose

	<pb facs="liv_020079_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/>you a legitimate receipt.
<lb/>I have written to <persName>Mrs
<lb/>Nichol</persName> thanking her for
<lb/>the 2nd donation towards
<lb/>my comfort.</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="1" unit="chars"/>Hoping you will enjoy
<lb/>your trip.</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="1" unit="words"/>I have the honor to remain
<lb/><space extent="1" unit="words"/><space extent="3" unit="chars"/>Yr. obt. servant,
<lb/><space extent="3" unit="words"/><persName>W. I. Craft.</persName></p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><persName>F.W. Chesson Esq.</persName>
<lb/><space extent="3" unit="chars"/><placeName>17 Kg. Wm. St.</placeName> <settlement>Strand.</settlement></p>

